messages.content: Diffree is a text-guided shape free object inpainting technique that utilizes a diffusion model.
How is Diffree implemented in ComfyUI?
Diffree is integrated as a custom node or plug-in in ComfyUI, allowing users to take advantage of its shape free object inpainting capabilities.
Why was the first_stage_downsample code removed from Diffree?
The first_stage_downsample code was removed from Diffree to simplify the codebase and improve performance.
What impact does ComfyUI's default K_diffusion have on K import?
ComfyUI's default K_diffusion setting can affect the import of K, particularly impacting portable packages. To avoid import failure, K_diffusion has been directly integrated into the plugin.
What are the requirements for installing ComfyUI_Diffree?
To install ComfyUI_Diffree, users need to clone the repository using git, ensure the required libraries are installed, and then run the installation command.
What should users use for the minimum input image size in ComfyUI_Diffree?
Users are advised to use an input image size of 512 pixels or similar, as the model was trained on 256 pixels.
What types of custom nodes or plug-ins are available in ComfyUI?

ComfyUI offers various custom nodes or plug-ins, including ParlerTTS, Llama3_8B, HiDiffusion, ID_Animator, StoryDiffusion, Pops, stable-audio-open-1.0, GLM4, CustomNet, Pipeline_Tool, Pic2Story, PBR_Maker, Streamv2v_Plus, MS_Diffusion, AnyDoor, Stable_Makeup, EchoMimic, FollowYourEmoji, Diffree, FoleyCrafter, and more.
